content: After almost 20 years its still the best Euchre interface I have found. While the chat platform is admittedly out of date, the table interface is visually pleasant and easy to use. The public games are generally social and offer a fun experience. Hardwood Euchre also features tournament leagues for a more challenging, competitive experience.

While Pogo and Yahoo on- line Euchre are far superior they don't have an Android version. I have found Hardwood to be the best on line euchre for androids but it is extremely frustrating. I have lost 16 or more games in a row - more than once - simply due to very poor app programming. It is not statistically valid to have a combo of 3 nines or tens and one or two Queens for 16 games in a row but Hardwood sets you up for failure unless you are one of their "chosen ones".  I don't know how to become one of their favorites (except by cheating - which I am told is very easy on Hardwood using "foom" signals - so try to avoid people that consistently play with the same partner). When the programmers' avatars are at the table, (and I don't mean the robots) you see some impossible combos (3 loners in a row for several games in a row). You'd think they'd get bored! Unlike Yahoo, Hardwood manipulates the cards so you can't go below a certain rating.  I would prefer more balance in the card programming and less interference from the Hardwood people. Now I just play Hardwood on my android to be amused by their crude and obvious programming manipulations.
